{
  "text": "Ectopic Hec1/Cdh Fzr affects mitotic-toendocycle but not endocycle-to-amplification transition After three rounds of endocycles, the follicle cells synchronously initiate a chorion gene amplification event that continues to increase the copy number of four different loci. The amplification occurs by the initiation of repeated rounds of DNA replication and fork movement to produce a gradient of amplified DNA extending ~100 kb [CITATION_1] OrrWeaver, 1991) . How the onset of the endocycle-toamplification transition is regulated is not understood.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5725433"
